1. Log in:
docker login

2. Tag your local image:
docker tag resume-app yourname/resume-app:v1

3. Push it:
docker push yourname/resume-app:v1
Replace yourname with your Docker Hub username.

Step 2: Create a Deployment
Create a file named:
resume-deployment.yaml

apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: resume-deployment
spec:
  replicas: 1
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: resume
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: resume
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: resume-container
        image: yourname/resume-app:v1
        ports:
        - containerPort: 80

Step 3: Create a Service
Create a file:
resume-service.yaml

apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: resume-service
spec:
  type: NodePort
  selector:
    app: resume
  ports:
  - port: 80
    targetPort: 80
    nodePort: 30080
    
Step 4: Apply the files
Run:
kubectl apply -f resume-deployment.yaml
kubectl apply -f resume-service.yaml

Step 5: Check everything
Check pods:
kubectl get pods
Check service:
kubectl get svc

Step 6: Open the app
Go to:
http://localhost:30080
